-- ING Investment Names Patrick Chia as Head of Asian Fixed Income
-- B y   K y o u n g w h a   K i m
-- 2012-02-15T05:03:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/ing-investment-names-patrick-chia-as-head-of-asian-fixed-income.html
ING Investment Management, a unit of
the biggest Dutch financial-services company, appointed Patrick
Chia as the head of its Asian Fixed Income division, it said in
a statement today.  Singapore-based Chia joins ING from Amundi Group and has
previously worked with DBS Asset Management, the Monetary
Authority of  Singapore  and Standard Chartered Plc, according to
the statement. The asset manager owned by  ING Groep NV (INGA)  manages
funds in the region including its pan-Asian bond fund and the
 ING Renta Fund Asian Debt fund , according to the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kyoungwha Kim in Singapore at 
